        "description": "I am currently working on a project that\u00a0 need to send the data in different processes. Instead of storing it in a file, I am using the IPC stream method, storing it into a buffer. When I try to send the data(bytes) through a socket, I loose the data in the client side. ( Which gives me the idea that when i leave the function(create buffer in the server side folder), I loose acces to that data. Can there be an example that explains this. \r\n\r\nAlso, can you implement a function that convert the record batch into the format that can be sent through the socket directly.\r\n\r\n\u00a0\r\n\r\nThe code are in the attachment, one for the server side code and the other for the client side code.\r\n\r\nThank you",
